"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1137515","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-07-16","<p>The UK's Trident II D5 missiles form part of a pool of available missiles shared with the US. The UK pays an annual contribution to the continued maintenance of the missile stock based on our share of the overall missile inventory.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2019-07-16T15:23:34.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1137515/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1137515/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1137515/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-07-08","Guided Weapons: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how long it would take, and at what cost, for her Department to procure a Trident D-5 missile.","false","Biography information for Anne-Marie Trevelyan","Berwick-upon-Tweed","Anne-Marie Trevelyan","274600"
