"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1137139","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-07-10","<p>This information would only be available at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>Legal aid funding is provided when the requisite eligibility criteria are met. Following consideration of claims for payment from the lawyers involved, all payments are made from a central legal aid budget, which is not demarcated according to any particular category of law.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2019-07-10T16:30:20.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1137139/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1137139/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1137139/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-07-05","Coroners: Legal Aid Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate he has made of the proportion of inquests for which legal aid was provided in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","273773"
